<description>Another product of the Atlas youth system, Jared left as he was given little opportunity to play in the first team by coach Marcelo Biesla. He left for Santos Laguna in 1996 and has developed into a very dangerous striker. 
At the 2002 World Cup finals, Jared scored the opening goal against Ecuador in Mexico's 2-1 win in Miyagi. He also scored the goal in the 1-1 draw with Italy in Oita that meant not only had Mexico qualified for the second phase but finished top of Group G.
Jared, who joined Bolton Wanderers in July 2005 with a two-year contract, was born on the same day as his Bolton colleague Jay Jay Okocha.</description>

